warning this is not a feel good question answer at your own risk hypothetically speaking if you had a life threatening illness and you knew there was a chance that you would die in the next year would you gather your loved ones together and discuss the reality of your situation or would you pretend that nothing's wrong counting on the chance that you might pull through i'd rather inform family and friends it's a lot easier on people if they are expecting a death and i'd could also tell each goodbye while i was still able i would let them know who i wanted my possessions to go to and let them know that i have donated my body to medical science Social rule Theory of conduct Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Goodness and value theory Socrates Drowning Pitaten Sexual orientation Friends Scientific method Epistemology Mojave people Yellow Ribbon campaign (Fiji) Jon Secada One Tree Hill (TV series) Abortion debate Gollum 2005 Kashmir earthquake The Invisibles Too Short a Season (TNG episode) Charmed Aristotle Obi-Wan Kenobi Aida (musical) Sin City Utilitarianism Grief Scientology beliefs and practices Ethics Knots Landing Micronauts Irony Practices of Jehovah's Witnesses Human sexual behavior Anderson Cooper Religious Society of Friends Forensics Consensus decision-making Muslim ibn Aqeel EastEnders Suicide Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Abortion Rent (musical) Plame affair Phaedo Time Out of Mind Humphrey Bogart SAT Extreme Programming Milton H. Erickson Doomsday argument Big Brother UK series 6 Autism Prostate cancer The Catcher in the Rye Quizbowl Risk Pedophilia God Charles Darwin's views on religion Life insurance The Two Doctors Normal distribution Mother Teresa Kurt Cobain Simone Weil Kill Bill Richard Rahl Aerial (dance move) Lucille Ball Spice Girls Rudolf Hermann Lotze Big Brother (USA TV series) Health insurance Novel Anorexia nervosa Randomness National Weather Service Philosophy Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan Reality Free will Meditation Cancer Probabili